{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington","content_id":"25bc81e5-2bf8-4326-9b98-42a0250ef9e6","description":"On the Duke of Newcastle: “Sir, you have a right to speak, but the House has a right to judge whether they will hear you.”","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Spencer Compton, Earl of Wilmington, was a successful Speaker of the House of Commons.  His tenure as First Lord of the Treasury was short and he died in office. He came to prominence after Sir Robert Walpole’s lengthy administration and was only ever seen as a temporary replacement.</p>\n\n<p>Read more about Spencer Compton, Earl of Wilmington, on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://history.blog.gov.uk/2014/12/03/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington/\" class=\"govuk-link\">History of government blog</a>.</p>\n</div>","born":"1673 or 1674, Compton Wynyates, Warwickshire","dates_in_office":[{"end_year":1743,"start_year":1742}],"died":"2 July 1743, St. James's Square, London","interesting_facts":"","major_acts":"","political_party":"Whig"},"document_type":"historic_appointment","first_published_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:36+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington","base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington","content_id":"25bc81e5-2bf8-4326-9b98-42a0250ef9e6","document_type":"historic_appointment","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:36Z","schema_name":"historic_appointment","title":"Spencer Compton, 1st Earl of Wilmington","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-compton-1st-earl-of-wilmington","withdrawn":false}],"ordered_related_items":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/hist